              "body": "![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)\n\nThe current implementation of `LoadFile` uses `os.ReadFile`, which reads the entire file into memory before checking its size against `MaxManifestSize`. If an extremely large file is provided, this could lead to memory exhaustion (OOM). It is safer to check the file size using `os.Stat` before attempting to read the content, especially since this PR includes security hardening for manifest loading.\n\n```suggestion\n\tfi, err := os.Stat(path)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"manifest: stat %q: %w\", path, err)\n\t}\n\tif fi.Size() > MaxManifestSize {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: manifest exceeds %d bytes (got %d)\", ErrInvalidManifest, MaxManifestSize, fi.Size())\n\t}\n\tb, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"manifest: read %q: %w\", path, err)\n\t}\n```",
