                "login": "copilot-pull-request-reviewer"
              },
              "body": "`LoadFile` enforces `MaxManifestSize` only *after* reading the entire file with `os.ReadFile`, so a very large manifest can still cause large allocations/IO before the size check triggers. To make the 1 MiB cap effective, consider checking file size via `os.Stat` first and/or reading via an `io.LimitReader`/`io.ReadAll` with a hard limit.",
