                "login": "copilot-pull-request-reviewer"
              },
              "body": "`cache.override` validation uses `strings.Contains(override, \"..\")`, which doesn't actually check for `..` *path segments* (e.g. it will incorrectly reject \"/var/..cache\" and may behave inconsistently across path separators/OSes). If the goal is to forbid traversal segments, split the cleaned path into elements and reject any element equal to \"..\" (or use a helper that validates paths segment-by-segment).",
