                "login": "copilot-pull-request-reviewer"
              },
              "body": "`scpToSSH` claims to accept and strip a leading \"/\" after the colon (e.g. `git@host:/owner/repo.git`), but `scpPattern` currently rejects any path that starts with `/`, so that branch is unreachable and those inputs will be rejected by `Canonicalize`. Either adjust the regex to allow an optional leading `/` in the scp path, or remove the comment/strip logic so the implementation and docs agree.",
