                "login": "copilot-pull-request-reviewer"
              },
              "body": "The StopAt ancestor check breaks when StopAt is the filesystem root (e.g. \"/\" on Unix): `stopAbs+sep` becomes \"//\", so `HasPrefix(cwdAbs+sep, stopAbs+sep)` is false and valid inputs are rejected. Consider using `filepath.Rel(stopAbs, cwdAbs)` (and ensuring it doesn't start with \"..\") or special-casing the root path instead of string prefix matching.\n```suggestion\n\t\trel, err := filepath.Rel(stopAbs, cwdAbs)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: StopAt %q is not an ancestor of cwd %q: %v\", ErrInvalidOptions, stopAbs, cwdAbs, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tsep := string(os.PathSeparator)\n\t\tif rel == \"..\" || strings.HasPrefix(rel, \"..\"+sep) {\n```",
