          "nodes": [
            {
              "id": "PRRC_kwDOSIQ0HM665J5d",
              "author": {
                "login": "chatgpt-codex-connector"
              },
              "body": "**<sub><sub>![P1 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P1-orange?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Treat dangling manifest symlink as an explicit error**\n\nThe discovery loop uses `os.Stat` and treats `ENOENT` as “no manifest here,” but a dangling `.aienv.yaml` symlink also yields `ENOENT`. That means a broken manifest symlink is silently skipped and `Find` can bind to an ancestor workspace instead of failing in place. In practice this can redirect subsequent sync/write operations to the wrong project root; the walk should detect an existing-but-invalid manifest entry (e.g., via `Lstat`) and return `ErrManifestNotRegular`.\n\nUseful? React with 👍 / 👎.",
              "createdAt": "2026-04-24T04:59:37Z",
              "url": "https://github.com/JustinBeaudry/aienvs/pull/1#discussion_r3135544925"
