              },
              "body": "**<sub><sub>![P2 Badge](https://img.shields.io/badge/P2-yellow?style=flat)</sub></sub>  Reject non-regular explicit manifest paths**\n\nWhen `--workspace` points directly to a `.aienv.yaml` path, `resolveExplicit` returns success without verifying the target is a regular file. FIFOs/sockets/devices with that basename are accepted, and later manifest reads can block or fail unpredictably (for example, reading a FIFO may hang). The explicit-file branch should apply the same regular-file validation used by the upward discovery path before returning a workspace.\n\nUseful? React with 👍 / 👎.",
